  "text": "η(2 − η). Here, in the analogy to the case of the nanotube, R represents the curvature [CITATION_1] (the geometrical meaning is also presented in Figure 11 ), A y is connected with the curvature of the carbon bonds. Next, γ and γ represent the nearest neighbor and the next-nearest neighbor hopping integrals, respectively and σ x ( r) = σ x cos ϕ − σ z sin ϕ. Here, σ x , σ y , σ z are the Pauli matrices, but (unlikely the τ matrices) this time they are connected with SOC. The parameters p and δ are connected with the hopping integrals and the atomic potential, respectively. Their closer explanation can be also found in [CITATION_2] . The following choice of their values was used: δ is of the order between 10 −3 and 10 −2 , ",
